      <div xml:id="NA138-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">iḵtu alar āyiṟṟu eṉa āṟṟāḷāya talaimakaṭkut talaivaṉ ciṟaippuṟamākat tōḻi colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what the confidante said to HER, who did not have the strength thinking there would be gossip, while HER was behind the fence.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA138">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            uvarviḷai yuppiṉ kuṉṟupōl kuppai</l>
<l>            malaiyuyttup pakaru nilaiyā vāḻkkaik</l>
<l>            kaṇaṅko ḷumaṇa ruyaṅkuvayi ṉoḻitta</l>
<l>            paṇṇaḻi paḻampār veṇkuru kīṉun</l>
<l>            taṇṇan tuṟaivaṉ muṉṉā ṇammoṭu </l>
<l>            pācaṭaik kalitta kaṇaikkā ṉeytaṟ</l>
<l>            pūvuṭa ṉeṟitaru toṭalai taiik</l>
<l>            kaṇṇaṟi vuṭaimai yallatu nuṇviṉai</l>
<l>            yiḻaiyaṇi yalkul viḻavāṭu makaḷir</l>
<l>            muḻaṅkutirai yiṉcīr tūṅku </l>
<l>            maḻuṅkaṉ mūtū raṟintaṉṟō viṉṟē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The noisy old village,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the sweet song of the thundering waves lingers(?)</l>
<l rend="indent2">with the women dancing for a festival, [their] hips adorned</l>
<l rend="indent2">with jewels of fine workmanship,</l>
<l rend="indent4">apart from seeing with the eye</l>
<l rend="indent">that<note place="foot">Actually this sentence is grammatically impossible to construe. The object of the act of seeing is <term xml:lang="ta">taii</term>, an absolutive. It ought to be a verbal noun here.</note> the man from the cool ghat, where the white heron gives</l>
<l rend="indent2">birth on an old [cart] bar ruined in service, cast off in [its]</l>
<l rend="indent4">weakened stage<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">uyaṅku vayiṉ</term> as an attribute to <term xml:lang="ta">vayiṉ uyaṅku</term> seems to make sense only if we take it as a kind of temporal clause ("cast off when it became weak"), though for such a thing we would like parallels.</note></l>
<l rend="indent2">by the salt-merchants going in groups of unstable living,</l>
<l rend="indent3">that bring to the mountains heaps [large] like hills</l>
<l rend="indent3">of salt ripened in brackish soil(?) [and] announce [the price],</l>
<l rend="indent">tied garlands with us on the previous day, stripping with [other]</l>
<l rend="indent">flowers round-stalked blue waterlilies swollen out of green leaves,</l>
<l rend="indent3">didn't know anything, did it?</l>
        </lg>
